data.text:
Not to be confused with Peterson.

PetersenPronunciationPeH-teHr-seHnOriginWord/nameNordicMeaning“son of Peter”Region of originScandinavia: Denmark, Norway, Sweden; Northern Germany: Former old Danish territories.Other namesVariant form(s)Peterson

Pettersen

Pedersen

Petersen is a common Danish patronymic surname, meaning "son of Peter". There are other spellings. Petersen may refer to:
